;=============================================================================
;+
; NAME:
;       p_cross
;
;
; PURPOSE:
;       Computes the cross products between the given arrays image points.
;
; CATEGORY:
;       UTIL/V
;
;
; CALLING SEQUENCE:
;       result = p_cross(p1, p2)
;
;
; ARGUMENTS:
;  INPUT:
;       p1:     An array of image points.
;
;       p2:     An second array of image points.
;
;
;  OUTPUT:
;       NONE
;
; RETURN:
;       Out-of-image components of the cross products.  The in-plane
;	components will always be zero.
;
;
; STATUS:
;       Completed.
;
;
; MODIFICATION HISTORY:
;       Written by:     Spitale	6/2005
;
;-
;=============================================================================
function p_cross, p1, p2

 z = p1[0,*,*]*p2[1,*,*] - p1[1,*,*]*p2[0,*,*]

 return, z
end
;===========================================================================
